GERMAN WINES

The beautiful valley of the Rhine produces unexcelled white wines, inimitable and famous since the days of antiquity. The valley is divided into three important wine-producing districts, the Rheingau, the Rheinhesse, and the Palatinate, a little to the south of the left bank. Wines of the Rheingau are the most celebrated, although the Rheinhesse produces some very noteworthy wines, and those of the Palatinate are distinctive with perhaps slightly more character.

The label of an especially fine wine will bear one of the follow- ing terms: ‘“‘Auslese’, a wine made from selected bunches of grapes; “Spatlese’’, a wine made from grapes gathered late in their period of ripening.
